						               													<description>When the quarantine ended, the people of the medieval villages poured out into the streets to celebrate with a great feast.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the sound of joyful songs, the clinking of glasses, and the clatter of dancing feet, all manner of evil spirits and devils crawled out of their holes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Anyone they knew could be a werewolf or a ghoul. The atmosphere is unhealthy!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Now ghouls drink the blood of babes in the comfortable streets of your cities, devils tempt monks, and knights prepare for battle with the dragon.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A new type of inhabitant has been added called UNHOLY CREATURE, these characters stand on a green background.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;They are mixed into the usual deck of suffering inhabitants, they can be drawn and, as usual, put into your town or into the town of your opponent.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Among all sorts of evil things, two special cards, a ghost and a werewolf, have been added to the Feasts and Devils expansion.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Now you can make your favorite resident immortal or turn a useless Leper into a ruthless and savage killer.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With the new addition you need to:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Disband all the Plague Doctors&amp;#10;     Put away the vials with the traces of epidemics&amp;#10;     Isolate the Leper&amp;#10;     Kick out all the useless peasants&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;But don't be sad, they'll be replaced by all kinds of evil and other characters!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A new holiday deck has been added. It has 13 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For example, the Bellethain Spring Festival requires each town to burn one of its inhabitants.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The old relics in Feasts and Devils have been replaced with new Cursed Relics.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
